import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd
def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['Year'] = pd.to_datetime(data['Year'], format='%Y', errors='coerce')
    data = data.sort_values(by='Year')
    plt.plot(data['Year'], data['Deaths'])
    plt.title('What is the trend of deaths over the years?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd
def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data = data.sort_values(by='Deaths', ascending=False)
    plt.bar(data['Entity'], data['Deaths'])
    plt.title('What is the distribution of deaths across different entities?', wrap=True)
    plt.xticks(rotation=90)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd
def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['Deaths'] = pd.to_numeric(data['Deaths'], errors='coerce')
    data = data.groupby('Entity').mean().sort_values(by='Deaths', ascending=False)
    fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(10, 6))
    ax.barh(data.index, data['Deaths'], color='blue')
    ax.axvline(data['Deaths'].mean(), color='red', linestyle='--', label='Average')
    ax.legend()
    plt.title('What is the average number of deaths per entity?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd
def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['Year'] = pd.to_datetime(data['Year'], format='%Y', errors='coerce')
    data = data.groupby(['Entity'])['Deaths'].sum().reset_index()
    data = data.sort_values(by=['Deaths'], ascending=False)
    fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(10, 6))
    ax.bar(data['Entity'], data['Deaths'], color='blue')
    ax.set_xlabel('Entity')
    ax.set_ylabel('Deaths')
    ax.set_title('What is the total number of deaths for each entity?')
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd
def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['Year'] = pd.to_datetime(data['Year'], format='%Y', errors='coerce')
    data = data.sort_values(by='Year')
    entities = data['Entity'].unique()
    fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(10, 6))
    for entity in entities:
        entity_data = data[data['Entity'] == entity]
        entity_data['Deaths'] = entity_data['Deaths'].pct_change()
        ax.plot(entity_data['Year'], entity_data['Deaths'], label=entity)
    ax.axhline(y=0, color='black', linestyle='--')
    ax.legend()
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
